Say hello to <b>BigDog</b>, our featured Citizen of the Week!<br><br>BigDog got out of the pound and moved to <a href="http://millsberry.com/home/?user=charlesman1023"><a href='/home/?user=charlesman1023'>20380-H Triumph Boulevard</a>, Metro Park</a> on October 1st, 2008. Since his move to Millsberry, he's been running free, and enjoying all that his Metro Park neighborhood has to offer. <br><br>The BigDog is very clever, a little caring, and charismatic. All that cleverness and caring comes in handy with two of his big favorite interests: math and animals. He should have no problem counting sheep!   <br><br>Another one of his interests is football. BigDog is quite the competitor on the field and he's got the trophy to prove it. Mastering Coach Danner's Tricky Touch Down has given him more than enough football skills to take it to the end zone.  <br><br>If you want to hang out with BigDog, and listen to some tunes, his favorite music is big band, pop, and rap. Whatever you play, it's sure to sound good through BigDog's state-of-the-art stereo system. <br><br>Next time you see BigDog, give him a high five and thank him for being such an outstanding citizen!</div>
